fields.description: Something Andrea and I have been working on. It came from playing Neil Young's "After The Goldrush" over scary chords and singing it like a Halloween song.
fields.name: In The Leaves In The Yard

fields.description:
The idea has been kicking around for a while, and will probably end up in the 2nd half of The Cool Forthcoming Album That Isn't Finished. "Please finish this song idea, other band members. I've lost my way," I said. 
My cat Chewy (Chewie? I guess I've never had to write it) was licking my toes the entire time I was tracking this demo. "Get outta here, fatso," I said.
fields.name: Chewy in the Stars / "I Let You In"

fields.description: This is me and John K. having fun on his 8 track about a month ago. He did the drum programming and the keyboards and I played the bass and did some computery stuff. We listened to it recently and decided it might be a good starting point for a Twin Sister song, so who knows what will become of it.
fields.name: Johnungle

fields.description: New demo of a new song.
fields.name: Levon and Chocolate Cake

fields.description: Yesterday, after giving chocolate covered strawberries to my two favorite celebs, Tracy Morgan and Bruce Willis, I just felt inspired to finish this idea we've had. Bryan and I started tracking. Today, Bryan gets a concussion / promotion at work, and weaving through his stuttering, slightly damaged thoughts is breaking news of Michael Jackson's death.  After Thriller and seeing people dance in front of the Apollo, we turned our thoughts to Japan and here you go.
fields.name: Kimmi In A Rice Field

fields.description: Bryan and I did this today while we were messing around with the Purchase drum samples for a couple of hours
fields.name: Sunday

fields.description:
http://vimeo.com/3793476

The Popular Guru shot and edited this really nice video of us playing at the Lit Lounge a couple of weeks ago. He's also put up some photos on Flickr that are worth a look. First, pretty photos, and now pretty videos. Lexis, we owe you a drink dude.
fields.name: Live Video + Photos from the Lit Lounge

fields.description: If Luna were a character on Twin Peaks, maybe this would be her theme music.
fields.name: Luna's Theme Music

fields.description: Also with Camera Head Shark and Psycho Rainbow, who were nice enough to record a big portion of our set that night. Tracks are Milk and Honey, Nectarine (Forest Cowboy version), I Want A House, and Daniel. Picture Andrea holding two beers during Daniel, because she was!
fields.name: April 9th @ Lit Lounge

fields.description: The title explains the key images evoked in the song.
fields.name: Space Babe/Rainforest Grüve

fields.description: Andrea and I singing this old folk song the way Nick Drake did with his sister.
fields.name: All My Trials

fields.description: Another song that started on the Casio (not to be confused with Andrea's Yamaha,  which is all over the EP and in many demos). This one will be in the Twin Sister live rotation as soon as our word-writers get around to it.
fields.name: Sister Smoke

fields.description: Some version of this may end up on the record, but we've been playing it very differently when we play it.
fields.name: Untitled

fields.description: The first inklings of a new idea.  It's called Filmi for now because part of the song is based on an Indian film song by RD Burman from the 70s.
fields.name: Filmi

fields.description: Bryan wrote and recorded a new idea!
fields.name: No Sleep

fields.description: Eric and Bryan recorded a new idea.  It sounds like a sister song to "Synth Jam."
fields.name: Smoke

fields.description: We just figured out how to play this tonight.
fields.name: All Around and Away We Go (2nd Demo)

fields.description: Gabe, Bryan, Eric, and I practiced together for the first time in months.  Even though Andrea wasn't around we managed to work on a lot.  The following recording is an excerpt from our space jam for the day.  I lost my space jam virginity.  It was special, intense, and over too soon.
fields.name: Space Jam (12/22/08)

fields.description: I was really sick when I sang this, apologies.  This one sounds really fun when we play it together.
fields.name: New Suit

fields.description: I recorded and wrote this in an hour or so after I got this sweet new Moog softsynth.  It's pretty obvious that I'm really excited about new keyboard sounds in this song.  It's a little goofy, but it was fun.
fields.name: Body Feels Strong

fields.description: The white bread version of "All Around and Away We Go". Just finished it now.
fields.name: White Bread

fields.description: Two years ago when I got this computer and recorded this song, I had recorded myself testing keyboard sounds after the track for about 7 minutes on accident.  I don't remember when or how the decision was made to build around that. You really ought to use headphones, it's much much better I think. I mixed the song a tad different too.
fields.name: Dry Hump (Extended Version)

fields.description: I don't know why this is called "#6". It's been named that way since I first recorded it. This melody has been through a couple different incarnations, including a more upbeat girl-group esque version. Feeling cramped as in that style, here it is as a lulled instrumental. It may stay this way, just cleaned up and re-tracked and everything.
fields.name: #6 (demo)

fields.description: In the summer of 2008 Eric and I began to experiment with guitar/keyboard loops.  One day, we had a loop I had made repeating in the room next to us and Eric noticed a simple kick and snare beat that could work.  After tracking drums and some bass, I then added a delayed keyboard track as well as an electric guitar track.  The title is taken from a song Udbhav had recorded about three years ago called "We Are Five."  For our upcoming full length album, we intend on re-tracking this and using the lead vocal part of "We Are Five" to create (we are seven?)  I don't know.  Either way, here it is!
fields.name: We Are Two

fields.description: Here is another one we have been working on for our shows coming up. This will be re-recorded with vocals soon. The bass was actually a separate song with the solo melody as the vocal melody, so we separated that and then put it together with an older song I had written.
fields.name: La la ya

fields.description: Since we started updating the site I've been waiting for Gabe to put up this amazing idea.  He hasn't joined in on the fun yet, so I'm putting it up for him.  We've been working on this one quite a bit at practice, it's going to be a jam!
fields.name: Synth Jam

fields.description: This here is a new song Andrea and I wrote about two months ago. This recording happened quickly, as it's only bass drums and some keyboards added by Bryan and Dev. There is a good chance a final version of this one will end up a B side to a single we'd like to release after the new year.
fields.name: All Around And Away We Go (demo)

fields.description: This is a very old song that Andrea wrote a few years ago. Just picture her singing it. Another contender for "Cool Forthcoming Album That Isn't Finished Yet".
fields.name: Compromise With A Gypsy

fields.description:
They're not new Twin Sister songs, but come on, we're not the only band on earth.

The mix attached here is mostly nice and slow, and unless I'm forgetting someone, it only has one male voice on it. It just happened that way.

It's dedicated to the hair styles pioneered by the Cocteau Twins. It doesn't have much to do with October.

Download!
fields.name: A Mix For October
